Complete start-new relaunch path + e2e tooling

CONTEXT
The reload-vs-start-new prompt was implemented on this branch in f950b2c via a
`confirmReload` callback in createSessionPersistence. A concurrent loop had
authored a parallel implementation (separate startup-controller module); that
duplicate was discarded in favor of the already-merged remote design (single
source of truth). This commit extends the remote design rather than replacing it.

GAPS CLOSED (vs spec acceptance criteria)
1. Start-new only cleared persisted storage + the stored directory handle. It
   left live in-memory filesystem workspace state (currentDirectoryHandle,
   workspaceName, workspaceFiles) intact, so a subsequent persist/restore could
   resurrect the abandoned folder. Now clearPersistedSession() also calls
   fsAPI.resetWorkspace() (new export -> clearWorkspace()).
2. Start-new did not load the default new-project state. Spec requires main.cpp +
   editorAPI.DEFAULT_SOURCE with no workspace. Added a startNewProject callback
   wired to toolbar.resetToNewProject() (actionNew body without the unsaved
   confirm). abandonForNewProject() = clearPersistedSession() + startNewProject().
3. test:e2e was broken on Node < 22.7: src/ui modules use ESM syntax in .js files
   which Node loads as CJS (cjs-module-lexer finds no named exports). Added
   --experimental-detect-module and included both suites.
4. CI ran only lint + build. Added a test:e2e step.

TEST FILE
scripts/e2e-session-restore-choice.test.mjs targets the confirmReload +
startNewProject API directly: reload-chosen re-requests readwrite and restores
live workspace; start-new clears session+handle+live-fs and loads default; next
persist after start-new records fresh source-only state (handle nulled by
resetWorkspace) not the abandoned workspace; snapshot-only still confirms before
restoring; source-only auto-restores with zero prompts; already-granted restores
with zero prompts.

SAFETY
startNewProject and fsAPI.resetWorkspace are optional (default no-op / guarded),
so the existing persistence suite and non-DOM contexts are unaffected. All 17
e2e tests + lint + build pass.
